ure faking. While it Is\ntrue that crocodiles frequently kill\nhuman beings for food, there Is no\ntruth In the swallowing alive fiction.\nDespite the orocodile\u2019s enormous\nmouth. Its throat is small. This ugly\nreptile finds it necessary to take small\npieces of food at one time, because of\nIts rigidly articulated jaw, and un\nelaetlc throat All its large prey must\nfirst be torn into little bits before Mr.\nor Mm- Crocodile can make a meal of\nIt. When the crocodile Is angry he\nbarks. He lives to a good old age\nand often paseea the century mark.\nIn old countries during the winter and\nin warm climates in times of drought\nthe crocodile* bury themselves In the\nmud from which they emerge upon\nthe return of prosperity. These rep\ntiles are tricky and have the advan\nDainty Gift China\nIn the Crowley-Milner Basement a\nIt Has Been Estimated By Our China Expert, Who Ought to Know,\ngji\u00dfini That--More Than Ten Thousand\n1 Pieces of China Are Here\nFrom Every Country On the Globe\nWhere China-Making Is An Art\nBs\\ (Sa^mmS\u00dfU\u00df It would be strange, would it not, if nothing could be found to give that\nBmfm China-loving friend of yours in such a vast collection as this?\nMB Prices are the Lowest in Every Instance >|\u00a7||||iiiMr\nNo One Rivals Us in China-Prices |ty|p\u00a7f\nThe Christmas Store\nWith the Little Prices\nTHE DETROIT TIKES! MONDAY. DECEMBER i*. 1910.\ntag# of being equally at home on land\nand in the wat#r. They often use\ntheir compressed, powerful tails as\nweapons with which they sweep their\nunsuspecting prey Into the water and\nhold them until they are drowned.\nThe ancient Egyptians used to wor\nship the crocodiles of the Nile and\nwhen these ugly reptiles died they\nwere embalmed. The monster croco\ndiles are now extinct and the foesl)\nancestors of the crocodile of todav,\nespecially the one known as the genus\nrhamposuchus of the Slwalik hill* of\nIndia, attained a length of over 50\nfeet\nThe crocodile usually leads a peace\nful, domestic existence, but when hun\ngry and no other food 1s to be had\nhe turns into a cannibal and eats his\nown babies.\nWhile the alligator Is of the croco\ndile family, it differs from the croco\ndile in a few* respects. The feet are\nleas webbed, and the bead Is shorter\nand flatter and he Is less aquatic. The\nhunters who are after the valuable\nskin, killed In the United States be\ntween 1880 and 1890 3,000,000 of these\nreptiles. Alligators are of slow*\ngrowth. At the age of 15 they are\nonly two feet long and if you ever see\na 12-foot alligator splashing around\nIn a zoo tank you can make up your\nmind that his age is about seventy-five\nand if he's longer than 12 feet he may\nbaa centenarian.\nThe sultan of Morocco believes that\ncertain members of legislative bodies\nshould have their ears cut off. Con\ngress meets Monday, Dec. 5.\nCrowley, Milner C& Company\nYULETIDE FAIR T TAL ES IS*\nFATHER AND MOTHER AND GRANDPA AND EVERYBODY.\nNANNETTE AND THE FAIRY CROW.\nA great steal millionaire\u2014that la,\na rich man who owned many big\nfactories which made steel rails, and\ncars, and wheels \u2014lived lu a mansion\nand had much money, which makes a\nmodern man great. H chad but one\nchild, a girl of eleven yeurs, who was\npretty enough and sweet enough, but\nwho was very, very stupid.\nHer Pittsburg parents called her;\nNannette because they had traveled\nin France. Once she beard her fath\ner and mother say how stupid she\nwas, so it made her sad and she wan\ndered about alone continually, often\nrefusing to even allow her nurse to\ngo with her. which they thought an\nother proof of her stupidity.\nOne morning ahe was walking in\nthe beautiful woods near home wheu\nshe heard her name\u2014\" Nannette.\nNannette\u201d\u2014a gain and again.\nThe little girl stopped under a\ngreat oak tree to listen.\n\u2018I am Nannette \u2014the stupid,\u201d she I\nmournfully replied.\n\u2018\u2018And 1 am Split-Tongue, the Talk\ning Crow,\u201d said a hoarse voice.\nNannette looked abuot her in won\nder. She could see neither crow*, nor\nman, nor woman, nor child \u2014nor any\nthing that resembled a fairy.\n(Nannette believed firmly lu fairies\nwhich made her hard-headed father\nsure that his child was stupid. But\nwe know people who believe in fair\nies are brightest of ell.)\nSuddenly a very black crow flew*\ntoward her, with a rustle and perch\ned on her left shoulder.\n\u201cMy dear, you are not stupid,\u201d said\nthe talking crow.\n\"Why, you can talk\u2014\u201d replied as\ntonished Nannette.\n\"Yes,'' said the crow\n\u201cAnd you are a crow,\u201d exclaimed\nNannette.\n\"Which proves that you are not so\nstupid as some people think.\u201d argued\nthe crow*, \u201cor you would not be sur\nprised.\u201d\nNanette's eyes began to shine with\nintelligence. Already ahe was a new*\nNannette.\nThe crow hopped to the ground,\nand Nannette saw a redheaded\nhunchbacked boy appear in the\norow's place.\n\u201cWhy\u2014why!\u201d cried Nannette.\n\"How 1 shall love to play with\nyou,\u201d Nannette said. \u201cBut,\" and sbo\nlooked sorry, \u201cI should like you so\nmuch better \u2014if\nNannette grew very mysterious, for\nshe bad a woman's soul.\nAnd the dwarf hunchback fairy im\nmediately turned into the moat beau\ntiful straight-limbed boy of fifteen\nthat little Nannette had ever seen!\n\u201cOs course,\u201d cried the girl child,\nstanding with her hands behind her,\n\u201cyou can be beautiful. If you can\nmake me wise.\u201d\nPlacing a bund on Nsnnette's\nshoulder the handsome boy kissed\nher on the forehead\n\u201cWe shall be playmates forever,\"\nhe said.\nAnd the child who had been stupid,\nbut who now understood many things,\n...nr-\u2014-I. ji.-r-T.-;- -\u2014\"\u2014A\n'it 1\nlearned in a few minutes, replied,\njoyfully:\n\u201cAdonis, you are wonderful! We\nshall be playmates. Come home with\nme. 1 shall tell my father; and he\nshall learn about things about which\nhe has never, never even heard\u2019\nAnd they started hand in hand to\nward the great mansion.\nLOW ROUND TRIP HOME SEEKERS\u2019 RATES TO FLORIDA\nltt a Pensacola and return $32.60\nv Tallahassee and return SUO\nIp Michigan Central\nGainesville and return 35.78\nDates of Sale, Dec. 20, Jan. 3 and 17,Feb. 7 and 21, Mar. 7 and 21 M..^ t b r J tu*n a nd r ,u,n \u00a32\nFull particulars at City Ticket Office, Detroit Opera House Block, West Palm Beach and return. 42J0\nand Station foot of Third St., or by writing. JOS. 8. HALL, Aset. Gen. Pass. Agent, Detroit.\nFor the convenience and, 1\ninformation of members of\nAll Hives in Detroit \u00abgj Wayne Cos.\nHeadquarters for the\nl. o. T. m. m.\nhave been established in the office of Michigan Tint,\nJones Building, 242 Griswold St\nTelephone, Main 1478-R,\nUnder the personal direction of\nMRS. MARY E. TIMMONY, member of Great Egeni\ntive Committee, and\nMRS. CARRIE GILBERT, Great Hive Auditor.\n9 to 12 a. m., 1 to 5 and 7:30 to 9:30 p. m.\nMembers will kindly bring old certificates.\nSUSPENDED MEMBERS ESPECIALLY INVITED\nTO CALL.\nFull information concerning Hive Cash Prize Content\nwill be given to each member.\nChristmas and New Year Holiday\nRates to All Canadian Points\nPast of Detroit and Port Arthur.\nOn* war lowest flr\u00abt-rla>\u00ab fare for the roaad trim. Gain r\nDec. 24, 25. 16; return limit Dec. \u2018.*7 Also Dec. 31. Jan. 1. 2;\nreturn limit Jan. 3, 1911.\nOne way lowest flrat-elasa fare and oae-thlrd far the\nround trie. Oolnu Dec. 21 to Jan 2: return limit Jan. 4, 1911.\nPCANADIAN 1\nha i\n\nAote Improved Trala Service. Leaving Detroit Union Depot, la. m. dallv\nexcept Sunday. 12 20 noon and 11:40 p. m. dally. Ticket Offices Uptown, 7\nFort-et. west, and Union Depot. Phones: Main 18H4; City 442.\nA. K. KDVOUDN, U. P. A.\nI\"jLis*Pwnwini\u00dfiiii\nThe Christmas Store\nWith the Little Prices\nPage Five","height":"30993","width":"22242"}}
